Hey - I've found 2 issues, and left some high level feedback:

- In the concurrent producer loop for `photonSideband` you added a bounds check only when clearing (`if (slot >= 0 && slot < photonSideband.Length)`), but not when initially writing; given that `slot` is bounded by the `for` loop and the array size, this check is redundantÔÇöeither remove it or apply it consistently to both write and clear if you genuinely expect out-of-range access.
- For the new `DateTime` constructions using `DateTimeKind.Unspecified` in `DrawORBox`, consider whether you actually want fully time-zone-agnostic values; if these are intended to participate in any conversions or comparisons across zones, you may want to use `DateTimeOffset` or an explicit `Utc`/`Local` kind instead to avoid subtle ambiguity later.

